<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Supplementary description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Female genitalia. Pygofer (Figs 34-35, 37) moderately sclerotised, 1.2 times longer than wide in caudal view. Anal tube (Figs 34, 36) short, shorter than wide in dorsal view, ventral margin slightly convex in lateral view; anal styles relatively short and small, strap-like. Gonapophysis VIII and IX and gonoplac (Figs 38-40) same as in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. acutata" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acutata">N. acutata</taxonomicName>
, while width of spiculated area approximately 1/8 of gonoplac, length of gonoplac 4.6 times of its width. Posterior vagina (Figs 41-42) stubby, with a long transverse sclerite near terminal, an irregular sclerite (left edge large and right edge small) and several circular or oval ones in dorsal view, without sclerite near base.
</paragraph>
