<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Female of 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. hamata" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="hamata">N. hamata</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. acutata" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acutata">N. acutata</taxonomicName>
sp. n., but differs in: (1) posterior vagina without sclerite near base (posterior vagina with two longitudinal sclerites near base in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. acutata" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acutata">N. acutata</taxonomicName>
); (2) anal tube shorter than wide in dorsal view (in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. acutata" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acutata">N. acutata</taxonomicName>
, anal tube longer than wide in dorsal view).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="25">The female genitalia of this species is described and illustrated for the first time.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
